# 5. Operating System Detection

## Objective

Identify the operating system of the target.

## Command

```bash
sudo nmap -O <TARGET-IP>
```

## Output File

```bash
sudo nmap -O <TARGET-IP> -oN raw-output/os-detection.txt
```

## Explanation

- `-O` enables OS fingerprinting.
- Estimates the operating system.
- Displays confidence level.

